						               													<description>In Masterplan, players take turns placing houses onto a 8x8 square grid. Houses can be placed at the sides or in the corners of the squares.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Whenever three houses are placed in such a way that a 4th house could make a row of 4 (no matter in which colour combination), a green park piece is placed where the 4th house could be placed. Players who have adjacent pieces to these new placed park(s) score at this moment. If a house is placed on the center of the sideline directly adjacent to this space (2 points) or at the corner (if diagonally adjacent, valued 2 points) or only on the adjacent space but at another line or corner (1 point).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Whenever a full square of houses could be build (3 houses creating an &amp;quot;L&amp;quot;) a tower is placed onto the fourth space. These towers score only at the end of the game, depending on the majority around them. (Same scoring as parks, but you don't actually score the points. Whoever would score the most points for a given Tower receives 2 points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Games ends after all houses are built and all towers are scored.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
